title: Watch: Ga. Tech stuns No. 9 FSU on blocked FG, 78-yard return
text:
Watch: Ga. Tech stuns No. 9 FSU on blocked FG, 78-yard TD return 
On Saturday Georgia Tech stunned No. 9 FSU, 22-16. Steve Mitchell / USA TODAY Sports Oct 24, 2015 at 10:37p ET 0Shares 
Georgia Tech won’t be making an appearance in the College Football Playoffs this season, and now ACC rival FSU may not be either. 
On Saturday, the Yellow Jackets handed the No. 9 Seminoles their first loss of the year when Lance Austin returned a blocked last-second, 55-yard field goal attempt by FSU’s all-American kicker Roberto Ayala to hand Georgia Tech a thrilling 22-16 victory. true 
The win snaps a five-game losing streak for the Yellow Jackets (3-5, 1-4 ACC), who began the year with CFP aspirations and a No. 16 ranking. 
Meanwhile, the loss all about guarantees FSU (6-1, 4-1 ACC) will not make the football version of the Final Four. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 0
